  "text": "In the saturated-mode, a charge deficit zone will appear at the drain-side gate edge [CITATION_1] . The gradual channel approximation is valid only in part of the entire intrinsic FET zone (Z 2 ) [CITATION_2] ; therefore, the current model developed from the linear-mode is difficult to expand to the saturation cases from physical insights. The following empirical saturatedmode I-V equation is introduced in this work [CITATION_3] , which can largely simplify the I-V model where λ is a fitting parameter, and I dsat is the critical saturation current when V ds = V dsat . This simple expression can ensure that I sat is equal to I dsat when V ds is equal to V dsat . The parameters and their values in the I-V model are summarized in Table 1 .",
